A woman? I thought to myself. That’s impossible. We’ve all been with each other for weeks, we would have known if one of us was a woman.

“You’re saying this is her?” The bandit motioned towards Demikas with his pistol. 

The gray wolf thrust his snout up into the air and took a whiff. “Yeah, that’s her. I told you I smelled something strange nearby, the scent of a bitch. This is her.”

