“You cannot keep a promise, no Stalker can keep their promises, let alone their pants on!” I could hear the venom in her voice.

I clenched my teeth, growing frustrated. She had only a little bit of time before I could no longer help her.

“Either you let me tend to your wounds, or you die. I don’t care if you do not trust me. We have fought side-by-side for many weeks. I’m not going to allow a friend to die if I can help it.”

She stopped her meager attempt to defend herself. She lay still for a bit, with her jacket ripped open and pants around her ankles.

