“C’mon, if I wanted to take advantage of you, I would have done so already,” I said, trying again to roll her over so that I could patch her wounds.

“It’s not about that anymore, you idiot,” she snarled. Was she really going to jeopardize her life for her pride?

“Now is not the time for shame.” I reminded her, setting my bag down. As a show of good faith, I pulled a clear bottle of rubbing alcohol, a pair of tweezers and some bandages out. “You are not the first woman I’ve seen before, you know. Don’t flatter yourself.”

She thought about it for a while, and with a great deal of reluctance and embarrassment, allowed me to roll her onto her back.

