I thought for a moment. I was here initially to make money to feed a drug habit. I had no professional skills, and no family keeping me out of trouble, but I did not feel like a daring bachelor. Most days I felt empty. The answer was not on my tongue or between my ears, so I looked into Demi’s eyes for an answer. I saw the fever glaze that was hanging to the golden marbles of her eyes. I saw the weariness. But I also saw the appreciation reflected in a look, and the trust that was now implicit. It was then that I knew why I was here.

